  "response_text": "# 3-Day Iron-Rich Meal Plan for Students\n\n## Day 1\n\n**Breakfast**\n- Fortified cereal with whole milk\n- Orange juice (vitamin C helps iron absorption)\n- Whole wheat toast with almond butter\n\n**Lunch**\n- Lean ground beef tacos with beans\n- Spinach salad with tomatoes\n- Brown rice\n\n**Dinner**\n- Baked salmon\n- Sweet potato\n- Steamed broccoli with lemon\n\n**Snacks**\n- Pumpkin seeds\n- Apple with peanut butter\n\n---\n\n## Day 2\n\n**Breakfast**\n- Oatmeal with raisins and cinnamon\n- Scrambled eggs\n- Strawberries\n\n**Lunch**\n- Lentil soup\n- Whole grain bread\n- Mixed greens salad with bell peppers\n\n**Dinner**\n- Chicken breast with herbs\n- Quinoa\n- Roasted kale\n\n**Snacks**\n- Dried apricots\n- Almonds\n\n---\n\n## Day 3\n\n**Breakfast**\n- Whole wheat pancakes\n- Turkey sausage\n- Blueberries\n\n**Lunch**\n- Tuna salad sandwich on whole wheat\n- Carrot sticks with hummus\n- Cantaloupe\n\n**Dinner**\n- Lean beef stir-fry\n- Brown rice\n- Bok choy and mushrooms\n\n**Snacks**\n- Dark chocolate (70%+)\n- Cashews\n\n---\n\n## Tips for Maximum Iron Absorption\n- ✓ Pair iron-rich foods with vitamin C sources\n- ✓ Avoid coffee/tea with meals (inhibits absorption)\n- ✓ Cook in cast-iron cookware when possible\n- ✓ Consult a doctor about supplementation if needed",
